I felt compelled to not only write this,but share this today in hopes that it helps even just one person to feel not so alone.It’s no secret I struggle with anxiety..I am an extremely happy,upbeat,positive,productive person-but then the other 10% of the time I just want to crawl out of my skin.

Don’t let social media fool you..yesterday was on those days when I was all glammed up doing a photoshoot but inside my heart was pounding and my body was frozen.I felt so much heartache and yet I had to smile through all of the pain.my mind was racing I thought it could explode..I felt so exhausted,drained,overwhelmed and hollow…numb.it was freaking scary !

I used to be cloaked in shame,afraid to tell others how much I was just struggling to get out of the bed..that I couldn’t find comfort in relationships..that I felt alone,hopeless,worthless…but that’s the thing about shame..it keeps us isolated!

Everytime we share our story..we can help others to see they are not alone in their battles..that we all need help sometimes.

All this to say..everyone has their own struggles,no one is alone & you should always reach out for help…oh and be kind,k?🤍

Bengali Tomato Khejur Chutney ♡
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
I have the most fondest memories of this dish.From Durga Puja to all Bengali celebrations,this gem has been a part of all❤️ It is a delicious sweet,spicy & tangy chutney made with tomatoes,whole spices,dates,raisins,tamarind & sugar.
I love using mustard oil for this recipe as it lends a pungent flavour which offsets the sweetness of the tomatoes & the sugar.You could also use jaggery if available🙂
